Many species form ectomycorrhizal associations, often occupying a dominant position in mycorrhizal communities. Other species are pathogens of many different plants and even lichens, and one species has even been suggested to form a lichen association with cyanobacteria. Yet more species are sparse and active decomposers, and a few are aquatic (Cannon & Kirk 2007)

Lindner DL)
